Library containing tools to record various ROS-related information to a MongoDB instance.
- rosout_logger listens to rosout messages and writes them to the db
- grep_log allows querying the stored rosout messages

Usage:
- In the background run mongod.  If you have the warehousewg stack, this can be done using
```
$ rosrun mongodb wrapper.py _database_path:=/path/to/db
```
- In a terminal,
    $ rosrun ros_logging rosout_logger
- Do your ros thing
- To query the log, use grep_log, e.g., if you want to find out when exactly your robot caught fire:
    $ rosrun ros_logging grep_log -m fire
